item.title: Info
item.description: I read once that the human mind never runs out of storage space – we forget only what we cannot retrieve. “caught in pointers” is an exhibition of digital print + analog silkscreen based paintings, 3d-scanned & printed sculptures, and painted laser engravings by Andrew CS — created in parallel to their debut album of the same name. pointers (*) index the world in RAM - we carry them in pockets & phone cases & microphones.
